(62, 1, '2015-02-22 23:21:00', '2015-02-22 23:21:00', 'Chad Healey is responsible for ensuring that projects come in on time and under budget. Chad oversees an average of 20 projects at a time, scheduling and attending onsite meetings, maintaining quality control and reviewing timelines with the contractor, architect and engineer.\r\n\r\nHis experience working for architectural and environmental firms in and around Boston, as well as developing construction plans and details for retail clients, provides him with a level of understanding and ability to “think outside of the box.” It is a skill set that arises from being part of a team in the early stages of the construction process.\r\n\r\nChad has overseen everything from ground-up new construction to expansions, renovations/additions and interior build outs. \r\n\r\nInvolvement begins at the onset with a review of construction documents, continuing on with coordination between bidding general contractors, acquiring building and demo permits, utility easements, construction, packaging closeout documentation and general landlord coordination, while handling hundreds of other details along the timeline.\r\nChad’s mission focus from the bidding process to final walkthrough—and all the steps in between—means there are no surprises and that we exceed our clients’ expectations.\r\n\r\nAttention to detail is a hallmark of T.M. Crowley & Associates.', 'Chad M. Healey', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'chad-m-healey__trashed', '', '', '2016-05-02 04:28:18', '2016-05-02 04:28:18', '', 0, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/?post_type=person&#038;p=62', 5, 'person', '', 0),
