(107, 1, '2016-02-01 02:32:48', '2016-02-01 02:32:48', 'Rob Antrim’s vast experience in development and tenant representation are examples of how T.M. Crowley & Associates provide clients with a unique perspective and comfort level for their next project.\r\n\r\nHaving worked closely with clients on development in 10 states, including such name brands as Target and PetSmart, Rob is thoroughly qualified and experienced in many facets of development.\r\n\r\nExperience, coupled with attention to detail, are among the traits that are universal to all members of T.M. Crowley & Associates.', 'Rob Antrim', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-01 02:32:48', '2016-02-01 02:32:48', '', 16, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/01/16-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(108, 1, '2016-02-01 02:34:07', '2016-02-01 02:34:07', 'AJ Barbato brings a track record of success for our clients. His expertise in ground up development includes every facet of the process from initial site selection through entitlement approvals, financing and the ultimate turnover of a successful project.  AJ has documented years of experience leading a team of brokers, client counsel, architectural and engineering firms as well as local municipalities, consistently driving projects to an ultimate successful completion.  \r\n\r\nHe has been intricately involved in development of numerous properties in Maine, New York, New Hampshire, Massachusetts, Connecticut, Indiana, Illinois and Wisconsin facilitating the growth of major corporations. \r\n\r\nWith a background in finance, AJ is perfectly positioned to make sure our clients receive the greatest return and the most value on their investment.  ', 'AJ Barbato', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '23-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-01 02:34:07', '2016-02-01 02:34:07', '', 23, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/01/23-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(109, 1, '2016-02-01 02:34:39', '2016-02-01 02:34:39', 'Mark Bettenhausen is an expert in the areas of Market Planning and Real Estate Research.\r\n\r\nHis experience and knowledge is the result of his position at Walgreen Company. During his 13 year tenure, Mark focused his talents on site selection, competitive intelligence and sales volume estimates for more than 600 new, relocated and remodeled Walgreen Company stores.\r\n\r\nHe has worked with Store Operations and Real Estate executives in the continental U.S. and Puerto Rico.\r\n\r\nIn the last three years of his tenure at Walgreen Company, he coordinated with Store Operators and Pharmacy Acquisitions. His responsibilities included solicitation, contract negotiation and valuation. Over 120 pharmacies were included in Mark’s responsibilities.\r\n\r\nHe now brings that experience, attention to detail and passion for his work to all of his efforts at T.M. Crowley & Associates.\r\nThe singular expertise of each member of our team is just one of the qualities that makes T.M. Crowley & Associates unique.', 'Mark Bettenhausen', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '26-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-01 02:34:39', '2016-02-01 02:34:39', '', 26, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/01/26-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(110, 1, '2016-02-01 02:35:09', '2016-02-01 02:35:09', 'Brenda Bryant is the executive administrative assistant for Tom Crowley.\r\n\r\nShe has been an administrative assistant for more than 26 years and has worked with Tom for 14 years. Brenda also provides administrative support for legal counsel, development and marketing.\r\n\r\nPrior to working for Tom Crowley, Brenda worked for 12 years at Simon Property Group, Indianapolis, Ind.\r\n\r\nAt T.M. Crowley & Associates, experience is one of our greatest assets.', 'Brenda Bryant', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '29-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-01 02:35:09', '2016-02-01 02:35:09', '', 29, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/01/29-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(111, 1, '2016-02-01 02:35:29', '2016-02-01 02:35:29', 'As COO, Chris brings over 20 years of experience in Financial Reporting, Project Budgeting, Operational Forecasts, Property Management, Financial Analysis and Cash Management, as well as Benefits Administration, 401k Compliance and Human Resources.\r\n\r\nChris works with key team members in the evaluation of potential developments. She assists in securing funding for ground-up development projects. In addition, Chris creates operational budgets and forecasts for multiple properties.\r\n\r\nShe also executes the day-to-day business transactions of the company as well as the administration of employee benefits, insurance, 401k plan and internal controls.\r\n\r\nChris is a licensed real estate broker.\r\n\r\nAt T.M. Crowley & Associates, we believe leadership is one of the keys to your success', 'Chris Daumeyer', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '36-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-01 02:35:29', '2016-02-01 02:35:29', '', 36, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/01/36-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(112, 1, '2016-02-01 02:36:19', '2016-02-01 02:36:19', 'Lou Eyster is part of our construction management team and is focused on facilitating all aspects of the project management and development process for our clients. This includes permitting, budget and schedule control, value engineering and construction.\r\n\r\nLou has more than seven years of experience working on large scale expansion and renovation projects serving both the public and private sector.\r\n\r\nHe is a LEED Accredited Professional and a licensed real estate broker.', 'Lou Eyster', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '54-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-01 02:36:19', '2016-02-01 02:36:19', '', 54, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/01/54-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(113, 1, '2016-02-01 02:36:34', '2016-02-01 02:36:34', 'As VP of Construction, Craig is responsible for managing the design, permitting and construction development process of both large scale and single tenant developments. Craig works closely with clients, architects and engineers, local and state regulatory agencies and contractors to complete construction projects from their inception all the way through completion of construction and delivery to the client. Craig oversees multiple projects at any given time and has proven capable of delivering multiple fast-pace projects on time by juggling responsibilities, managing non-flexible schedules, providing quick problem solution and effectively managing the client’s needs while exceeding their expectations.\r\n\r\nCraig is a Licensed Professional Engineer.', 'Craig Forgey', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '56-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-01 02:36:34', '2016-02-01 02:36:34', '', 56, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/01/56-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(114, 1, '2016-02-01 02:36:56', '2016-02-01 02:36:56', 'Paul Guay brings a wealth of knowledge and a history of success to every project that he oversees.\r\n\r\nPaul is responsible for the successful implementation of all aspects of construction. His expertise encompasses forecasting, planning, scheduling, budgeting, as well as tracking and reporting.\r\n\r\nHe is a respected team manager with geographical experience that ranges from all the New England states, through the upper East Coast to the Midwest, including Illinois, Missouri, Indiana and Wisconsin.\r\n\r\nHis oversight of land possession, due diligence, town planning approvals, permitting, tracking and scheduling all aspects of a project, creates a comfort level for clients that is unmatched in the development sector.\r\n\r\nHe has an extensive track record, not the least of which is his involvement with Bank of America. Under his guidance, Paul provided real estate planning, strategy and implementation services to key lines of business within the bank.\r\n\r\nPaul managed the Environmental and Mobile Engineering Group for the bank’s Corporate Real Estate Group. Under his guidance, he managed four million square feet of space with annual occupancy costs of $300 million.\r\n\r\nHe also led a project team in the build out and startup of a 150,000 square foot, $25 million call center. The project was completed ahead of schedule and five percent under budget.\r\n\r\nThere are many other success stories associated with his leadership. As a key member of our team, Paul’s experience and vision are more reasons why clients turn to T.M. Crowley & Associates for their next project.', 'Paul Guay', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '58-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-01 02:36:56', '2016-02-01 02:36:56', '', 58, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/01/58-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(115, 1, '2016-02-01 02:37:20', '2016-02-01 02:37:20', 'Charlie Haapala is an expert in construction, design and development. He has a wealth of experience in retail fast track, and brand name store roll outs across the country. His history of success includes the establishment of restaurants, department stores, strip centers, mixed use high-rise and loft conversions, town housing, high end residential, hotels, banks, downtown parking garages, office buildings and warehouses.\r\n\r\nCharlie has been integral to the fast track, high volume (+100) simultaneous competitive bid build outs of Lerner’s, Express, The Limited, Victoria’s Secret, Lane Bryant, Lens Crafters, Wilson Suede & Leather, Tucci Benucchi Restaurants, Capitol Commerce Center, Forest Park Mall, J. Alexander Restaurants, Carson Pirie Scott, Barnes & Noble Book Seller and more.\r\n\r\nAs Managing VP of Construction for a Chicagoland developer, Charlie has been responsible for delivering completed projects, including initial site and building design development, specification detailing, city/neighborhood approvals, conceptual budgeting/estimating, contract negotiation and administration, management of in-house construction staff, consultants, architects, engineers, contractors, customer service departments, property management and claim settlements.\r\n\r\nHe successfully delivered more than $80 million in development during this two year phase, including over 375 condos with numerous commercial tenant spaces.\r\n\r\nCharlie has earned a reputation for delivering high quality projects on time and on budget. He is there every step of the way, from initial conceptual budgeting, competitive hard bidding, contract negotiations and award, project management through completion and customer service.\r\n\r\nAt T.M. Crowley & Associates, each member of our team has a history of excellence.', 'Charlie Haapala', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '60-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-01 02:37:20', '2016-02-01 02:37:20', '', 60, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/01/60-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(116, 1, '2016-02-01 02:37:48', '2016-02-01 02:37:48', 'Chad Healey is responsible for ensuring that projects come in on time and under budget. Chad oversees an average of 20 projects at a time, scheduling and attending onsite meetings, maintaining quality control and reviewing timelines with the contractor, architect and engineer.\r\n\r\nHis experience working for architectural and environmental firms in and around Boston, as well as developing construction plans and details for retail clients, provides him with a level of understanding and ability to “think outside of the box.” It is a skill set that arises from being part of a team in the early stages of the construction process.\r\n\r\nChad has overseen everything from ground-up new construction to expansions, renovations/additions and interior build outs. \r\n\r\nInvolvement begins at the onset with a review of construction documents, continuing on with coordination between bidding general contractors, acquiring building and demo permits, utility easements, construction, packaging closeout documentation and general landlord coordination, while handling hundreds of other details along the timeline.\r\nChad’s mission focus from the bidding process to final walkthrough—and all the steps in between—means there are no surprises and that we exceed our clients’ expectations.\r\n\r\nAttention to detail is a hallmark of T.M. Crowley & Associates.', 'Chad M. Healey', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '62-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-01 02:37:48', '2016-02-01 02:37:48', '', 62, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/01/62-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(117, 1, '2016-02-01 02:38:13', '2016-02-01 02:38:13', 'Cody Herbster’s primary focus is the Third Party Development program for T.M. Crowley & Associates.\r\n\r\nHis experience in Sales and Marketing for an industrial manufacturer gave him a base on which to build his skills and offer advice and counsel to our clients as they navigate the development process.\r\n\r\nHis history of success adds to the value that clients of T.M. Crowley & Associates expect.', 'Cody Herbster', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '64-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-01 02:38:13', '2016-02-01 02:38:13', '', 64, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/01/64-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(118, 1, '2016-02-01 02:38:52', '2016-02-01 02:38:52', 'As Regional Real Estate Deal Manager at T.M. Crowley & Associates, Chris brings a background of managing and overseeing a portfolio of over 65 projects in the New England and New York areas. He has over 15 years of experience in commercial real estate.\r\n\r\nChris acts as a liaison between clients and a development team consisting of environmental consultants, civil engineers, architects, general contractors and attorneys. His primary goal is delivering projects on schedule.\r\n\r\nChris is also responsible for coordinating purchase agreement and lease signings, tracking operative dates from execution through closing/possession, initiating environmental due diligence and coordinating the entitlement process with civil engineers, architects and attorneys. His responsibilities also include ensuring compliance with client requirements, issuing monthly tracking reports on all projects, adherence to timelines/schedules and assimilating closing and possession documentation for outside legal counsel.', 'Chris Moretti', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '68-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-01 02:38:52', '2016-02-01 02:38:52', '', 68, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/01/68-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
