(125, 1, '2016-02-01 02:40:28', '2016-02-01 02:40:28', 'Sandra brings over 20 years of experience in administrative executive support as well as customer service and market research reporting. She is a graduate of Indiana University and has enjoyed a career in merchandising and management as well as executive administration. Her attention to detail and ability to serve many different support functions within the company make her a highly efficient and valued employee of T.M. Crowley & Associates.', 'Sandra Ritter', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '74-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-01 02:40:28', '2016-02-01 02:40:28', '', 74, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/01/74-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(126, 1, '2016-02-01 02:40:40', '2016-02-01 02:40:40', 'As VP of Real Estate Development with T.M. Crowley & Associates, Tracey partners with various retail clients through our Preferred Developer program. She is responsible for new store site selection in territories throughout the six New England states and New York.\r\n\r\nAs part of our Preferred Developer program, T.M. Crowley & Associates provides a single point of accountability, centralizing the client’s real estate objectives, strategies and responsibilities for the markets they serve.\r\n\r\nTracey oversees and manages her territory from the initial identification of new markets and site opportunities, to completion of the project and store opening.\r\n\r\nThis timeline includes the tasks of contract negotiation, coordinating due diligence, obtaining local municipality approvals and permits, compiling and scheduling possession and closing — all while maintaining the project schedule and budget, and delivering stores as promised to the client.\r\n\r\nHer experience, expertise and attention to detail make her a valuable asset to the work we do and the clients we serve.\r\n\r\nAt T.M. Crowley and Associates, our blueprint for success involves every member of our team giving 100%, 100% of the time.', 'Tracey J. Roll', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '76-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-01 02:40:40', '2016-02-01 02:40:40', '', 76, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/01/76-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(127, 1, '2016-02-01 02:40:55', '2016-02-01 02:40:55', 'As VP Controller with T.M. Crowley & Associates, Pamela is responsible for overseeing the accounting operations of several real estate development subsidiaries. She also provides project accounting management for several national clients.\r\n\r\nPamela works closely with client financial managers, construction and real estate personnel and vendors to foster successful business relationships. Pamela is involved with each project from the initial budgeting to the final construction closeout process.\r\n\r\nPamela has 12 years experience in project accounting management, consisting primarily of new ground up stores, renovations and expansions. Her responsibilities have involved over 500 stores throughout the country.\r\nShe coordinates with construction personnel, civil engineers, environmental consultants and architects to provide an accurate budget estimate per project to submit for approval. All accounting of project presentation, entitlement procurement and construction costs are managed on a project-by-project basis and processed through T.M. Crowley & Associates.\r\n\r\nAttention to detail is a trademark of T.M. Crowley & Associates.', 'Pamela Whitaker', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '78-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-01 02:40:55', '2016-02-01 02:40:55', '', 78, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/01/78-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(128, 1, '2016-02-01 02:41:19', '2016-02-01 02:41:19', 'Jason Challand utilizes his wealth of experience by advising clients on their real estate needs. He is a trusted advisor on site selection, land assemblage, contractual negotiations, due diligence, analyzing bids from contractors and builders, project supervision and communication with local governing bodies. Jason is also responsible for facilities acquisition and disposition, tenant and landlord representation, investment and land sales.\r\n\r\nHis expertise is an asset to clients who are considering ownership, investment or leasing. He has created development projects and closed sale and lease transactions that have exceeded $730 million in value.\r\n\r\nJason’s knowledge base includes Tenant/Buyer & Landlord/Investor Advisory Services, Investment Sales and Land Acquisition, as well as Disposition Services. He is a Licensed Indiana Real Estate Broker.\r\n\r\nJason has worked with companies and developers such as Gershman Brown Crowley, Throgmartin Henke Development, Mainstreet Property Group, i3 Worldwide, Level 3 Communications, Midwest Graphics, BremnerDuke Healthcare, Duke Realty, Edgeworth Laskey Properties, First Industrial Realty Trust, Opus North, The Estridge Companies, Fischer Homes, Beazer Homes, NVR/Ryan Homes, Mann Properties, Somerset Financial Services, Krieg DeVault LLP, Doninger Tuohy & Bailey LLP, Nelson & Frankenberger P.C., The Mediation Alternative, Wise Financial, Meyer Najem, The Fazzt Race Team, Five Guys Burgers and Fries, Buffalo Wild Wings, Moe’s Southwest Grill, Taco Bell/Southern Bells, Inc., Hot Box Pizza, Fifth Third Bank, First Merchants Bank and all land planning departments in Indianapolis and the surrounding counties.\r\n\r\nAt T.M. Crowley & Associates, we bring a team of proven professionals to your project.', 'Jason S. Challand', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '82-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-01 02:41:19', '2016-02-01 02:41:19', '', 82, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/01/82-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
