(160, 1, '2016-02-04 05:54:11', '2016-02-04 05:54:11', 'Megan Painter is the Accounts Payable Manager for T.M. Crowley & Associates.\r\n\r\nHer duties include submitting and tracking all pre-construction draws and land deposit payments for approval. When draws are funded, she processes payments to the vendors and land owners in a timely manner.\r\nHer scope of responsibilities stretches from the New England states to the Midwest. She is accountable for T.M. Crowley & Associates’ monthly invoices, rental payments and ACH deposits. She participates in monthly conference calls with vendors to review A/R reports.\r\n\r\nMegan also supports our Marketing Department. Megan is a liaison between the client and a project team. The team consists of attorneys, signage vendors, brokers, architects and engineers.\r\n\r\nMegan’s primary focus in her work with the Marketing Department is the on-time delivery of the tour books. The tour books include maps, aerials, site photos, competition profiles and demographic packages associated with our projects.\r\n\r\nAt T.M. Crowley & Associates, our team’s diverse skills work to your advantage.', 'Megan Painter', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '70-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-04 05:54:11', '2016-02-04 05:54:11', '', 70, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/04/70-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(161, 1, '2016-02-04 05:54:18', '2016-02-04 05:54:18', 'As VP Controller with T.M. Crowley & Associates, Pamela is responsible for overseeing the accounting operations of several real estate development subsidiaries. She also provides project accounting management for several national clients.\r\n\r\nPamela works closely with client financial managers, construction and real estate personnel and vendors to foster successful business relationships. Pamela is involved with each project from the initial budgeting to the final construction closeout process.\r\n\r\nPamela has 12 years experience in project accounting management, consisting primarily of new ground up stores, renovations and expansions. Her responsibilities have involved over 500 stores throughout the country.\r\nShe coordinates with construction personnel, civil engineers, environmental consultants and architects to provide an accurate budget estimate per project to submit for approval. All accounting of project presentation, entitlement procurement and construction costs are managed on a project-by-project basis and processed through T.M. Crowley & Associates.\r\n\r\nAttention to detail is a trademark of T.M. Crowley & Associates.', 'Pamela Whitaker', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '78-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-04 05:54:18', '2016-02-04 05:54:18', '', 78, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/04/78-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(162, 1, '2016-02-04 05:54:21', '2016-02-04 05:54:21', 'As VP of Construction, Craig is responsible for managing the design, permitting and construction development process of both large scale and single tenant developments. Craig works closely with clients, architects and engineers, local and state regulatory agencies and contractors to complete construction projects from their inception all the way through completion of construction and delivery to the client. Craig oversees multiple projects at any given time and has proven capable of delivering multiple fast-pace projects on time by juggling responsibilities, managing non-flexible schedules, providing quick problem solution and effectively managing the client’s needs while exceeding their expectations.\r\n\r\nCraig is a Licensed Professional Engineer.', 'Craig Forgey', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '56-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-04 05:54:21', '2016-02-04 05:54:21', '', 56, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/04/56-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(163, 1, '2016-02-04 05:54:26', '2016-02-04 05:54:26', 'Paul Guay brings a wealth of knowledge and a history of success to every project that he oversees.\r\n\r\nPaul is responsible for the successful implementation of all aspects of construction. His expertise encompasses forecasting, planning, scheduling, budgeting, as well as tracking and reporting.\r\n\r\nHe is a respected team manager with geographical experience that ranges from all the New England states, through the upper East Coast to the Midwest, including Illinois, Missouri, Indiana and Wisconsin.\r\n\r\nHis oversight of land possession, due diligence, town planning approvals, permitting, tracking and scheduling all aspects of a project, creates a comfort level for clients that is unmatched in the development sector.\r\n\r\nHe has an extensive track record, not the least of which is his involvement with Bank of America. Under his guidance, Paul provided real estate planning, strategy and implementation services to key lines of business within the bank.\r\n\r\nPaul managed the Environmental and Mobile Engineering Group for the bank’s Corporate Real Estate Group. Under his guidance, he managed four million square feet of space with annual occupancy costs of $300 million.\r\n\r\nHe also led a project team in the build out and startup of a 150,000 square foot, $25 million call center. The project was completed ahead of schedule and five percent under budget.\r\n\r\nThere are many other success stories associated with his leadership. As a key member of our team, Paul’s experience and vision are more reasons why clients turn to T.M. Crowley & Associates for their next project.', 'Paul Guay', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '58-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-04 05:54:26', '2016-02-04 05:54:26', '', 58, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/04/58-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
