(169, 1, '2016-02-04 06:01:25', '2016-02-04 06:01:25', 'Lou Eyster is part of our construction management team and is focused on facilitating all aspects of the project management and development process for our clients. This includes permitting, budget and schedule control, value engineering and construction.\r\n\r\nLou has more than seven years of experience working on large scale expansion and renovation projects serving both the public and private sector.\r\n\r\nHe is a LEED Accredited Professional and a licensed real estate broker.', 'Lou Eyster', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '54-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-04 06:01:25', '2016-02-04 06:01:25', '', 54, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/04/54-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(170, 1, '2016-02-04 06:01:29', '2016-02-04 06:01:29', 'As Regional Real Estate Deal Manager at T.M. Crowley & Associates, Chris brings a background of managing and overseeing a portfolio of over 65 projects in the New England and New York areas. He has over 15 years of experience in commercial real estate.\r\n\r\nChris acts as a liaison between clients and a development team consisting of environmental consultants, civil engineers, architects, general contractors and attorneys. His primary goal is delivering projects on schedule.\r\n\r\nChris is also responsible for coordinating purchase agreement and lease signings, tracking operative dates from execution through closing/possession, initiating environmental due diligence and coordinating the entitlement process with civil engineers, architects and attorneys. His responsibilities also include ensuring compliance with client requirements, issuing monthly tracking reports on all projects, adherence to timelines/schedules and assimilating closing and possession documentation for outside legal counsel.\r\n\r\nAt T.M. Crowley & Associates, we believe there is no substitute for experience and a proven track record of success.', 'Chris Moretti', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '68-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-04 06:01:29', '2016-02-04 06:01:29', '', 68, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/04/68-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(171, 1, '2016-02-04 06:01:32', '2016-02-04 06:01:32', 'As VP of Real Estate Development with T.M. Crowley & Associates, Tracey partners with various retail clients through our Preferred Developer program. She is responsible for new store site selection in territories throughout the six New England states and New York.\r\n\r\nAs part of our Preferred Developer program, T.M. Crowley & Associates provides a single point of accountability, centralizing the client’s real estate objectives, strategies and responsibilities for the markets they serve.\r\n\r\nTracey oversees and manages her territory from the initial identification of new markets and site opportunities, to completion of the project and store opening.\r\n\r\nThis timeline includes the tasks of contract negotiation, coordinating due diligence, obtaining local municipality approvals and permits, compiling and scheduling possession and closing — all while maintaining the project schedule and budget, and delivering stores as promised to the client.\r\n\r\nHer experience, expertise and attention to detail make her a valuable asset to the work we do and the clients we serve.\r\n\r\nAt T.M. Crowley and Associates, our blueprint for success involves every member of our team giving 100%, 100% of the time.', 'Tracey J. Roll', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '76-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-04 06:01:32', '2016-02-04 06:01:32', '', 76, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/04/76-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
