(174, 1, '2016-02-09 02:50:12', '2016-02-09 02:50:12', 'As Regional Real Estate Deal Manager at T.M. Crowley & Associates, Shannon’s responsibilities include managing numerous projects for national clients in the Midwest and New England areas.\r\n\r\nShannon acts as a liaison between our clients and development teams consisting of attorneys, civil engineers, environmental consultants, architects and general contractors. Shannon ensures the projects remain on schedule and deliverables are met on time.\r\n\r\nShannon’s responsibilities also include overseeing the coordination of the purchase and sale agreements or lease signings and tracking operative dates from their execution through closing/possession, at which time she coordinates the assimilation of the closing/possession documents for the client’s outside counsel.\r\nShannon is also responsible for initiating the due diligence process with the environmental consultants and coordinating the entitlement process with civil engineers, architects and attorneys to ensure compliance with the client’s requirements.\r\nShe works closely with the engineers, architects and attorneys through the permitting process to ensure the project remains on schedule. Project tracking reports are issued monthly to ensure adherence to timelines and to provide project updates to the team.\r\n\r\nAt T.M. Crowley & Associates, all of us take a 360-degree view of our responsibilities. Our combined vision creates a picture-perfect result for our clients.', 'Shannon Parker', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '72-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-09 02:50:12', '2016-02-09 02:50:12', '', 72, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/09/72-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(175, 1, '2016-02-09 02:51:15', '2016-02-09 02:51:15', 'As VP of Real Estate Development with T.M. Crowley &amp; Associates, Tracey partners with various retail clients through our Preferred Developer program. She is responsible for new store site selection in territories throughout the six New England states and New York.\r\n\r\nAs part of our Preferred Developer program, T.M. Crowley &amp; Associates provides a single point of accountability, centralizing the client’s real estate objectives, strategies and responsibilities for the markets they serve.\r\n\r\nTracey oversees and manages her territory from the initial identification of new markets and site opportunities, to completion of the project and store opening.\r\n\r\nThis timeline includes the tasks of contract negotiation, coordinating due diligence, obtaining local municipality approvals and permits, compiling and scheduling possession and closing — all while maintaining the project schedule and budget, and delivering stores as promised to the client.\r\n\r\nHer experience, expertise and attention to detail make her a valuable asset to the work we do and the clients we serve.\r\n\r\nAt T.M. Crowley and Associates, our blueprint for success involves every member of our team giving 100%, 100% of the time.', 'Tracey J. Roll', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '76-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-09 02:51:15', '2016-02-09 02:51:15', '', 76, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/09/76-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(176, 1, '2016-02-09 02:53:05', '2016-02-09 02:53:05', 'Lou Eyster is part of our construction management team and is focused on facilitating all aspects of the project management and development process for our clients. This includes permitting, budget and schedule control, value engineering and construction.\r\n\r\nLou has more than seven years of experience working on large scale expansion and renovation projects serving both the public and private sector.\r\n\r\nHe is a LEED Accredited Professional and a licensed real estate broker.', 'Lou Eyster', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '54-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-09 02:53:05', '2016-02-09 02:53:05', '', 54, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/09/54-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
