(178, 1, '2016-02-11 02:25:36', '2016-02-11 02:25:36', 'Cody Herbster’s primary focus is the Third Party Development program for T.M. Crowley & Associates.\r\n\r\nHis experience in Sales and Marketing for an industrial manufacturer gave him a base on which to build his skills and offer advice and counsel to our clients as they navigate the development process.\r\n\r\nHis history of success adds to the value that clients of T.M. Crowley & Associates expect.', 'Cody Herbster', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '64-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-11 02:25:36', '2016-02-11 02:25:36', '', 64, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/11/64-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(179, 1, '2016-02-11 02:26:00', '2016-02-11 02:26:00', 'Paul Guay brings a wealth of knowledge and a history of success to every project that he oversees.\r\n\r\nPaul is responsible for the successful implementation of all aspects of construction. His expertise encompasses forecasting, planning, scheduling, budgeting, as well as tracking and reporting.\r\n\r\nHe is a respected team manager with geographical experience that ranges from all the New England states, through the upper East Coast to the Midwest, including Illinois, Missouri, Indiana and Wisconsin.\r\n\r\nHis oversight of land possession, due diligence, town planning approvals, permitting, tracking and scheduling all aspects of a project, creates a comfort level for clients that is unmatched in the development sector.\r\n\r\nHe has an extensive track record, not the least of which is his involvement with Bank of America. Under his guidance, Paul provided real estate planning, strategy and implementation services to key lines of business within the bank.\r\n\r\nPaul managed the Environmental and Mobile Engineering Group for the bank’s Corporate Real Estate Group. Under his guidance, he managed four million square feet of space with annual occupancy costs of $300 million.\r\n\r\nHe also led a project team in the build out and startup of a 150,000 square foot, $25 million call center. The project was completed ahead of schedule and five percent under budget.\r\n\r\nThere are many other success stories associated with his leadership. As a key member of our team, Paul’s experience and vision are more reasons why clients turn to T.M. Crowley & Associates for their next project.', 'Paul Guay', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '58-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-11 02:26:00', '2016-02-11 02:26:00', '', 58, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/11/58-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(180, 1, '2016-02-11 02:26:08', '2016-02-11 02:26:08', 'As COO, Chris brings over 20 years of experience in Financial Reporting, Project Budgeting, Operational Forecasts, Property Management, Financial Analysis and Cash Management, as well as Benefits Administration, 401k Compliance and Human Resources.\r\n\r\nChris works with key team members in the evaluation of potential developments. She assists in securing funding for ground-up development projects. In addition, Chris creates operational budgets and forecasts for multiple properties.\r\n\r\nShe also executes the day-to-day business transactions of the company as well as the administration of employee benefits, insurance, 401k plan and internal controls.\r\n\r\nChris is a licensed real estate broker.\r\n\r\nAt T.M. Crowley & Associates, we believe leadership is one of the keys to your success', 'Chris Daumeyer', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '36-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-11 02:26:08', '2016-02-11 02:26:08', '', 36, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/11/36-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(181, 1, '2016-02-11 02:26:16', '2016-02-11 02:26:16', 'As VP of Construction, Craig is responsible for managing the design, permitting and construction development process of both large scale and single tenant developments. Craig works closely with clients, architects and engineers, local and state regulatory agencies and contractors to complete construction projects from their inception all the way through completion of construction and delivery to the client. Craig oversees multiple projects at any given time and has proven capable of delivering multiple fast-pace projects on time by juggling responsibilities, managing non-flexible schedules, providing quick problem solution and effectively managing the client’s needs while exceeding their expectations.\r\n\r\nCraig is a Licensed Professional Engineer.', 'Craig Forgey', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '56-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-11 02:26:16', '2016-02-11 02:26:16', '', 56, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/11/56-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(182, 1, '2016-02-11 02:26:21', '2016-02-11 02:26:21', 'Rob Antrim’s vast experience in development and tenant representation are examples of how T.M. Crowley & Associates provide clients with a unique perspective and comfort level for their next project.\r\n\r\nHaving worked closely with clients on development in 10 states, including such name brands as Target and PetSmart, Rob is thoroughly qualified and experienced in many facets of development.\r\n\r\nExperience, coupled with attention to detail, are among the traits that are universal to all members of T.M. Crowley & Associates.', 'Rob Antrim', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-11 02:26:21', '2016-02-11 02:26:21', '', 16, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/11/16-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(183, 1, '2016-02-11 02:26:28', '2016-02-11 02:26:28', 'Brenda Bryant is the executive administrative assistant for Tom Crowley.\r\n\r\nShe has been an administrative assistant for more than 26 years and has worked with Tom for 14 years. Brenda also provides administrative support for legal counsel, development and marketing.\r\n\r\nPrior to working for Tom Crowley, Brenda worked for 12 years at Simon Property Group, Indianapolis, Ind.\r\n\r\nAt T.M. Crowley & Associates, experience is one of our greatest assets.', 'Brenda Bryant', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '29-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-11 02:26:28', '2016-02-11 02:26:28', '', 29, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/11/29-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(184, 1, '2016-02-11 02:26:33', '2016-02-11 02:26:33', 'As VP Controller with T.M. Crowley & Associates, Pamela is responsible for overseeing the accounting operations of several real estate development subsidiaries. She also provides project accounting management for several national clients.\r\n\r\nPamela works closely with client financial managers, construction and real estate personnel and vendors to foster successful business relationships. Pamela is involved with each project from the initial budgeting to the final construction closeout process.\r\n\r\nPamela has 12 years experience in project accounting management, consisting primarily of new ground up stores, renovations and expansions. Her responsibilities have involved over 500 stores throughout the country.\r\nShe coordinates with construction personnel, civil engineers, environmental consultants and architects to provide an accurate budget estimate per project to submit for approval. All accounting of project presentation, entitlement procurement and construction costs are managed on a project-by-project basis and processed through T.M. Crowley & Associates.\r\n\r\nAttention to detail is a trademark of T.M. Crowley & Associates.', 'Pamela Whitaker', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '78-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-11 02:26:33', '2016-02-11 02:26:33', '', 78, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/11/78-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(185, 1, '2016-02-11 02:26:38', '2016-02-11 02:26:38', 'Jason Challand utilizes his wealth of experience by advising clients on their real estate needs. He is a trusted advisor on site selection, land assemblage, contractual negotiations, due diligence, analyzing bids from contractors and builders, project supervision and communication with local governing bodies. Jason is also responsible for facilities acquisition and disposition, tenant and landlord representation, investment and land sales.\r\n\r\nHis expertise is an asset to clients who are considering ownership, investment or leasing. He has created development projects and closed sale and lease transactions that have exceeded $730 million in value.\r\n\r\nJason’s knowledge base includes Tenant/Buyer & Landlord/Investor Advisory Services, Investment Sales and Land Acquisition, as well as Disposition Services. He is a Licensed Indiana Real Estate Broker.\r\n\r\nJason has worked with companies and developers such as Gershman Brown Crowley, Throgmartin Henke Development, Mainstreet Property Group, i3 Worldwide, Level 3 Communications, Midwest Graphics, BremnerDuke Healthcare, Duke Realty, Edgeworth Laskey Properties, First Industrial Realty Trust, Opus North, The Estridge Companies, Fischer Homes, Beazer Homes, NVR/Ryan Homes, Mann Properties, Somerset Financial Services, Krieg DeVault LLP, Doninger Tuohy & Bailey LLP, Nelson & Frankenberger P.C., The Mediation Alternative, Wise Financial, Meyer Najem, The Fazzt Race Team, Five Guys Burgers and Fries, Buffalo Wild Wings, Moe’s Southwest Grill, Taco Bell/Southern Bells, Inc., Hot Box Pizza, Fifth Third Bank, First Merchants Bank and all land planning departments in Indianapolis and the surrounding counties.\r\n\r\nAt T.M. Crowley & Associates, we bring a team of proven professionals to your project.', 'Jason S. Challand', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '82-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-11 02:26:38', '2016-02-11 02:26:38', '', 82, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/02/11/82-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
