(194, 1, '2016-02-14 20:10:10', '2016-02-14 20:10:10', 'Randy brings more than 25 years of executive leadership and business development expertise in private industry, non-profit and government sectors to his role as general council and principal.  As a seasoned professional in both domestic and international business, he provides guidance in all phases of business operations and real estate development, including site selection, incentive negotiations, finance, project management, legal affairs and government relations. He has led efforts to acquire and develop more than one million square feet of real estate valued at more than $250 million.\r\n\r\nPreviously, Randy served as the Executive Assistant for Economic Development to the Mayor of Bloomington, Indiana, where he co-authored legislation that created special economic zones to aid in the redevelopment of brownfield sites. He received his Doctor of Law and Bachelor of Arts degrees from Indiana University, and has served on the board of numerous community and economic organizations. ', 'Randy Lloyd', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'randy-lloyd__trashed', '', '', '2016-05-02 04:28:18', '2016-05-02 04:28:18', '', 0, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/?post_type=person&#038;p=194', 2, 'person', '', 0),
