(224, 1, '2016-05-02 04:33:47', '2016-05-02 04:33:47', 'Pete Carbone, Senior Vice President for HTI Cancer Centers / Proton International, is a seasoned professional with over 25 years’ experience in the Real Estate Development, Design and Construction field. He currently is responsible for a range of development initiatives including Facility Development, Construction and Design. Pete joined HTI Cancer Centers / Proton International in 2013 and was drawn to the company because of the mission to increase the availability of cancer treatment and proton therapy to the many patients who can benefit from advanced treatments and therapies. Prior to joining HTI Cancer Centers / Proton International, Pete spent the past 18 years in the design and development departments of several Hospitals and Healthcare Systems in South Florida in addition to most recently leading the Facility Development at ProCure Treatment Centers helping bring proton therapy to four major cities in the USA. He is a veteran of leading major projects and has collectively managed over $2.5 billion in total projects. He has also worked for a major oil company for 6 years as Construction and Maintenance Engineer and spent 5 years active duty in the United States Air Force as a Construction Engineer. He is also a registered General Contractor, a Certified Healthcare Facility Manager (CHFM) and a Certified LEED Green Associate. Pete has a Mechanical Engineering degree from Norwich University and a Masters of Business Administration from Nova Southeastern University.', 'Pete Carbone', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'pete-carbone', '', '', '2016-05-02 04:33:47', '2016-05-02 04:33:47', '', 0, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/?post_type=person&#038;p=224', 4, 'person', '', 0),
