(226, 1, '2016-05-02 04:34:15', '2016-05-02 04:34:15', 'Mr. Beranek has more than 37 years of experience with Healthcare and highly technical Facility Design, Construction, Programing, and joined PI in February 2014. Previously and most recently he was responsible for the successful design/construction/occupancy of four Proton Cancer Treatment Centers for Procure in the United States each valued between $30M-$35M- more than any other single entity worldwide He now leads the design and construction management for the new Proton Center at University Medical Center in Groningen, The Netherlands for PI. He has developed new project and program delivery processes and instilled them into the Design Build Teams processes that redefine “successful project delivery”. This new process results with Team members that develop a specific culture that manages with precision AND has fun at the same time. He is a graduate of Purdue University with a BS in Construction Management and also from Indiana University with an MS in Business and Public Management.', 'Jay Beranek', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'jay-beranek', '', '', '2016-05-02 04:34:15', '2016-05-02 04:34:15', '', 0, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/?post_type=person&#038;p=226', 5, 'person', '', 0),
