(262, 1, '2015-10-19 04:21:23', '2015-10-19 04:21:23', '<strong>Chicago—October 19, 2015</strong>—Loop Capital has teamed with Proton International to support and promote the construc- tion, development and advancement of one-room proton therapy centers. An innovative, risk-reducing cancer treat- ment, proton therapy is positioned and designed to be one of the most technologically advanced methods of treating cancerous tumors. Its laser-sharp precision delivers protons of high-level radiation exactly where it is needed, cutting down on radiation exposure to vital organs in and around the cancerous location.\r\n\r\nPrinciples of Proton International (PI) have spent the past two decades successfully implementing nearly one dozen specialized centers around the nation, which offer this leading-edge treatment. Now, through its relationship with Loop Capital, an investment banking, brokerage and advisory firm, PI is making it easier and more affordable for hospitals, oncologists and other medical professionals to penetrate the proton market. Medical providers can offer top-of-the line treatment to cancer patients with one-room centers in a much more convenient way through non-recourse financing structures. Clinical partners who leverage the combined expertise of PI and Loop Capital benefit from having a knowl- edgeable and experienced team backing and supporting their proton center project.\r\n\r\nInstead of building mega centers, which often take years to construct and $100-200 million in capital and financing to secure, PI’s one room center mitigates financial risks with the addition of a single room to a pre-existing radiation oncology clinic, or through transforming existing property to a proton therapy center. By offering a turnkey solution model with financing solution, backed by future revenue, PI and Loop Capital make proton therapy more accessible to medical providers and healthcare systems across the nation.\r\n\r\nClick here to view the official <a href="http://protonintl.com/images/news/Proton%20Loop%20Press%20Release%2010-19.pdf" target="_blank">PDF VERSION</a> of the press release.\r\n\r\n<strong>About Proton International</strong>\r\n\r\nProton International is a project oriented proton therapy development company providing innovative and experienced based develop- ment and operational services. Team members have successfully developed multiple proton centers with our services focused on busi- ness planning, design, financing, equipment selection, project management, training and ongoing support of operations.\r\n\r\nFor media or general inquiries: Kristen Chandler, Director of Sales and Marketing, <span id="cloak20300"><a href="mailto:kchandler@protonintl.com">kchandler@protonintl.com</a></span>, (502) 939-3323.\r\n\r\n<strong>About Loop Capital</strong>\r\n\r\nFounded in 1997, Loop Capital is an investment bank, brokerage and advisory firm that provides creative capital markets solutions for corporate, governmental and institutional entities across the globe. Loop Capital Markets and its affiliates serve clients in corporate and public finance, financial advisory services, taxable, tax-exempt and global equity securities sales and trading, transition manage- ment and analytical services.\r\n\r\nHeadquartered in Chicago, the firm has 21 additional offices located in Atlanta, Baltimore, Charlotte, Cleveland, Dallas, Denver, Detroit, Hartford, Houston, Indianapolis, Los Angeles, Miami, New Orleans, New York, Newark Oakland, Pensacola, Philadelphia, San Francisco, Washington D.C. and West Palm Beach.\r\n\r\nFor media or general inquiries: Jorian Seay, Marketing &amp; Communications Associate, <span id="cloak58939"><a href="mailto:jorian.seay@loopcapital.com">jorian.seay@loopcapital.com</a></span>, 312-913-2205.\r\n\r\n<em><em>Loop Capital® is a registered trademark of Loop Capital Holdings, LLC. Securities and investment banking services are offered through Loop Capital Markets LLC. Loop Capital Markets LLC is a registered broker-dealer and a member of the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority</em></em>', 'PRESS RELEASE: Loop and PI''s Exclusive Relationship for Non-Recourse Financing to Make One-Room Proton Facilities', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '262', '', '', '2016-05-04 04:22:07', '2016-05-04 04:22:07', '', 0, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/?p=262', 0, 'post', '', 0),
