o determine and share best practices</li>\r\n 	<li>KPI reporting on all critical system performance metrics as determined by your center</li>\r\n 	<li>Coordination of ongoing physics quality and commissioning services, and oversight of all quality equipment calibration and maintenance</li>\r\n 	<li>Oversight and coordination of any third party contracted services</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSuccessfully operating a flourishing proton therapy center requires expertise, attention to detail and experience in managing through common obstacles. Our team brings more experience to the table than any other, and our operational services ensure your center operates at its greatest capacity.', 'Operations', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '271-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-04 22:49:08', '2016-05-04 22:49:08', '', 271, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/05/04/271-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(273, 1, '2016-05-04 22:50:30', '2016-05-04 22:50:30', 'We’re committed to providing access to proton therapy that benefits patients and providers alike. We offer your patients the ability to immediately access proton therapy, while providing a cost effective solution for building your own center. We are the most experienced and seasoned group in the industry, capable of handling portions of therapy center development, or all of it - including financing, design, construction, staffing, operation and maintenance of the facilities.\r\n\r\nTo ensure your project is completed on budget, on time and to the highest standards, our team of experts offers assistance and/or full management in the following areas:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Business planning and feasibility: We work with you to develop a business plan and proforma specific to your clinical program, business assumptions and unique needs.</li>\r\n 	<li>Organizational structure: We work with your team to identify and define the organizational structure needed to fulfill project goals and objectives. The ownership structure we create supports finance strategy, the development of services and the ongoing operational strategy, assuring you maintain control and meet your financial obligations.</li>\r\n 	<li>Financing: Our financing solutions provide an effective, low cost path that limits your balance sheet impact. We employ a strategic finance structure that provides funding for projects at a level close what you could borrow on your own, but with a significantly lesser balance sheet impact.</li>\r\n 	<li>Real estate, building design and construction: Proton therapy centers are complex undertakings. Our industry expertise and our partnership with nationally renowned developers, <a href="http://tmcrowley.com">T.M. Crowley &amp; Associates</a>, ensures you don’t have to worry about obstacles related to the design, construction and setup of your therapy center. Simply put, we’ve been here before - and with projects of this scale, experience translates to cost savings and efficiency.</li>\r\n 	<li>Equipment selection, purchase and maintenance: From installation and systems integration to the ongoing maintenance of your equipment, we use our expertise to ensure your center is designed and maintained in a way that maximizes your investment and delivers the best possible patient experience.</li>\r\n 	<li>Ongoing support services: Once your therapy center is built, the key to success lies in high quality standards, a highly competent staff, a comprehensive medical program in place, treatment protocols and a research program for clinical trial participation. We offer comprehensive ongoing support services designed to ensure every aspect of the ongoing management of your center results in efficient operation and positive outcomes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe benefits of having a proton therapy center are significant, but to successfully build and maintain one, you must possess deep expertise, experience and resources. That’s where we come in. Whether you need help with a singular aspect of your proton therapy center development, or start-to-finish project management, we should be your first call.', 'Assured Access', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '269-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-04 22:50:30', '2016-05-04 22:50:30', '', 269, 'http://mattritter.design/protonintl/2016/05/04/269-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
